Pop the @British chicken thighs{8} into a #bowl{} and sprinkle over the @cumin seeds{2}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{some}. Add @olive oil{1%tbsp} and the zest from the @lemon{1}. Mix well and leave the chicken to marinate while you chop all the veggies.

Cut the @red onion{1}(cut in half through the root, peeled and sliced into thin half moon shapes) in half through the root, peel and then slice each half into thin half moon shapes. Chop the @celery stick{2}(chopped into 1cm wide chunks) into 1cm wide chunks. Peel the @carrots{2}(peeled, cut in half lengthways and sliced at 1cm intervals), cut in half lengthways and then slice at 1cm intervals. Peel the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated on the fine side of a grater) and grate on the fine side of your #grater{}.

Heat a #frying pan{} and #large saucepan{} on high heat. Add @olive oil{1%tbsp} to each pan and when the olive oil is hot, fry the chicken thighs in the frying pan for ~{3%minutes} on each side. You want them to be golden brown. Whilst you brown the chicken thighs, add your chopped onions, celery and carrots to the #saucepan{} and cook for ~{5%minutes} until soft. Lower the heat after ~{2%minutes} to stop your veggies from burning.

When the chicken thighs are brown, add them to the vegetables in the saucepan. Add the garlic and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Pull the leaves from the @marjoram{3}(leaves pulled from stalks) stalks and add half of them to the saucepan.

Now add the @tomato passata{1} and then refill the carton with water three times and add this to the pan with 1 of the @chicken stock pot{2}. Bring to the boil, stir well to dissolve the chicken stock pot and then reduce the heat to medium-low. Cook for ~{25%minutes} with the lid off.

> The chicken is cooked when the centre is no longer pink.

While your tagine cooks, prepare the couscous. Bring 600ml of water to the boil in a #pot{} and stir in the other chicken stock pot. Season with @salt{to taste} and @black pepper{to taste}, add @olive oil{1%tbsp} and the remaining marjoram. Pour in the @couscous{1.5}, remove the pot from the heat and cover with a #lid{} or #plate{}. Leave for ~{10%minutes}. Have a quick clean down, do any washing up and then finish off your last couple of jobs. Drain the @chickpeas{1%400g can} into a #colander{} and rinse with cold water. Rinse the @baby spinach{1%bag}.

When the tagine is ready, add the chickpeas and spinach to the saucepan and mix well. Simmer for another ~{1%minute}, check the seasoning and add a pinch more salt and black pepper if you feel it needs it. Finish with a squeeze of lemon juice and serve immediately with the couscous.